HEADWORD: Bootikin
<hw>Boot"i*kin</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[<ets>Boot</ets>
+ <ets>-kin</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A little boot, legging, or
gaiter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A covering for the foot or hand, worn as a cure for
the gout.</def> <rj><au>H. Walpole.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Booting</ent>⟦br⟧
